                            <h6 class="fw-bold">Project Evolution</h6>
                            <p class="mb-2">This amazing project was a challenge given to us by the Turtle Shelter Project charity as a final semester project in our Information Systems program at BYU. They let us help make some of the vests before starting, which helped us understand their mission and needs. The goal was to help create a potential new website for the charity while building our skills. We built the entire application in just 4 days and presented our work to both industry professionals and judges. We are very proud of the work we did and are grateful for the opportunity to work with the Turtle Shelter Project.</p>
                            <p class="mb-2">It originally started as a fully functional web application deployed on AWS with:</p>
                            <ul class="mb-3">
                                <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> Node.js deployed on AWS Elastic Beanstalk with automated CodePipeline from GitHub</li>
                                <li><strong>Database:</strong> Amazon RDS PostgreSQL with normalized schema design</li>
                                <li><strong>Security:</strong> Custom domain with HTTPS encryption and secure data access</li>
                                <li><strong>Email System:</strong> Custom AWS email server for automated notifications</li>
                                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Tableau dashboard integrated for admin analytics with auto-updating data</li>
                                <li><strong>Features:</strong> Complete user authentication, volunteer management, donation processing integration, event coordination</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="mb-2">For educational purposes, it has been converted to this <strong>demo version</strong> with a cost-effective home server setup:</p>
                            <ul class="mb-3">
                                <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Docker container running on a home server with nginx reverse proxy, Cloudflare CDN, and domain managed by Cloudflare (transferred from Porkbun)</li>
                                <li><strong>Data:</strong> Static demo data (no database connection)</li>
                                <li><strong>Educational Focus:</strong> Demonstrates real-world web development from production deployment to cost-effective hosting</li>
                                <li><strong>Technologies:</strong> Node.js, Express.js, EJS templating, Bootstrap 5</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="mb-0"><small class="text-muted">This demonstrates the complete development lifecycle from production deployment to educational demo.</small></p>
                            
